        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "All sunk and dim her eyes so bright, Her form decay'd by pining, Till through her wasted hand, at night, You saw the taper shining. By fits a sultry hectic hue Across her cheek was flying; By fits so ashy pale she grew Her maidens thought her dying.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
