        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "GATHERING SONG OF DONALD THE BLACK.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000004_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000004_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Come from deep glen, and From mountain so rocky; The war pipe and pennon Are at Inverlochy. Come every hill plaid, and True heart that wears one, Come every steel blade, and Strong hand that bears one.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000006_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000006_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Come as the winds come, when Forests are rended, Come as the waves come, when Navies are stranded: Faster come, faster come, Faster and faster, Chief, vassal, page and groom, Tenant and master.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000008_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000008_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "SIR w SCOTT.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000010_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000010_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "A wet sheet and a flowing sea, A wind that follows fast And fills the white and rustling sail And bends the gallant mast; And bends the gallant mast, my boys, While like the eagle free Away the good ship flies, and leaves Old England on the lee.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000011_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000011_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "O for a soft and gentle wind! I heard a fair one cry; But give to me the snoring breeze And white waves heaving high; And white waves heaving high, my lads, The good ship tight and free- The world of waters is our home, And merry men are we.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000013_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000013_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "A. CUNNINGHAM.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000015_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000015_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Ye Mariners of England That guard our native seas! Whose flag has braved, a thousand years The battle and the breeze! Your glorious standard launch again To match another foe: And sweep through the deep, While the stormy winds do blow; While the battle rages loud and long And the stormy winds do blow.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000016_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000016_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "The spirits of your fathers Shall start from every wave- For the deck it was their field of fame, And Ocean was their grave: Where Blake and mighty Nelson fell Your manly hearts shall glow, As ye sweep through the deep, While the stormy winds do blow; While the battle rages loud and long And the stormy winds do blow.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000017_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000017_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Britannia needs no bulwarks, No towers along the steep; Her march is o'er the mountain waves, Her home is on the deep. With thunders from her native oak She quells the floods below- As they roar on the shore, When the stormy winds do blow; When the battle rages loud and long And the stormy winds do blow.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000018_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000018_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "The meteor flag of England Shall yet terrific burn; Till danger's troubled night depart And the star of peace return. Then, then, ye ocean warriors! Our song and feast shall flow To the fame of your name, When the storm has ceased to blow; When the fiery fight is heard no more, And the storm has ceased to blow.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000019_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000019_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "T. CAMPBELL.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000020_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000020_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "BATTLE OF THE BALTIC.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000021_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000021_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Of Nelson and the North Sing the glorious day's renown, When to battle fierce came forth All the might of Denmark's crown, And her arms along the deep proudly shone; By each gun the lighted brand In a bold determined hand, And the Prince of all the land Led them on.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000022_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000022_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Like leviathans afloat Lay their bulwarks on the brine; While the sign of battle flew On the lofty British line: It was ten of April morn by the chime: As they drifted on their path There was silence deep as death; And the boldest held his breath For a time.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000023_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000023_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "But the might of England flush'd To anticipate the scene; And her van the fleeter rush'd O'er the deadly space between. \"Hearts of oak!\" our captains cried, when each gun From its adamantine lips Spread a death shade round the ships, Like the hurricane eclipse Of the sun",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000024_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000024_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Again! again!",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "very high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000025_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/1367/291968/1367_291968_000025_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1367",
        "content": "Out spoke the victor then As he hail'd them o'er the wave, \"Ye are brothers! ye are men! And we conquer but to save:-- So peace instead of death let us bring: But yield, proud foe, thy fleet With the crews, at England's feet, And make submission meet To our King.\"",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "very slow",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-1367_291968_000027_000000",
